// expected_exit: 42
// summary: Catter-derived test. Catter (the original Vale-to-Rust interop proof of
// concept, vendored at /Catter/) imports both rust.std.option.Option and rust.std.vec.Vec
// in the same program and uses Vec<int>.with_capacity(42).capacity() — that multi-import
// shape including Option is not covered by any other test. ri_16 covers Vec + String,
// not Vec + Option, and Option's bindings have historically regressed (Catter's
// /Catter/bindings/std/option/ shows it once worked); a test here catches the binding
// import compiling at all. Method body matches Catter's main.vale but returns the
// capacity via exit code instead of println (the test runner runs --no_std true).

import rust.std.option.Option;
import rust.std.vec.Vec;

exported func main() int {
  vec = Vec<int>.with_capacity(42i64);
  return vec.capacity().TruncateI64ToI32();
}
